This is the way to reproduce the problem.

1. From Internet Explorer generate a Time Tracking Report. Click on 'Excel View' and the file opens.
2. If instead of clicking on 'Excel view', we right click, and add it to favorites, when we try to access the file from the bookmark, IE cannot open the file. The same happens when you access the file typing the URL directly.

The exact error message is

{noformat}
Internet Explorer cannot download <URL> from <HOST>
Internet Explorer was not able to open this Internet site. The requested site is either unavailable or cannot be found. Please try again later.
{noformat}

Typing the URL or using a bookmark works in Safari and Firefox.

Doing packet inspection on the requests/reponses shows that the HTTP GET request is basically the same. The only difference in that the successful request has an additional parameter.

{noformat}
Referer: http://xxxx:8080/secure/ConfigureReport.jspa?versionId=-1&sortingOrder=least&completedFilter=all&selectedProjectId=10284&reportKey=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.reports%3Atime-tracking&Next=Next
{noformat}

See attached files for both successful and failed requests.

Packet inspection shows that tomcat actually serves the file back in both cases. Once the file is sent back, we can see in both successful and failed cases that the OS sends an TCP ACK back to tomcat.

The error only happens for Time Tracking Reports. Other excel sheets, like the ones generated from filters, work fine.

